  "texts": [
    "In terms of touchpoints with the DSA, the Data Act's Chapter II on business-to-consumer and business-to-business data sharing complements the DSA's focus on transparency and access for researchers.",
    "Yet tensions could emerge around expanded data access if the Data Act's provisions extend platforms' content moderation duties or noticeand-takedown responsibilities under the DSA Article 14.",
    "Consistency among Member States Despite the theoretical discussion upheld throughout this text, we yet shall be cognizant that difficulties might arise in generalizing research findings across the sociotechnical diversity of platforms and national contexts within the EU's Member States.",
    "Individual platforms have distinct technical affordances, algorithmic architectures, business models and user demographics that shape how disinformation manifests and spreads [6, 36, 77].",
    "Additionally, the establishment of national Digital Service Coordinators (DSCs) under Article 38 of the DSA, tasked with national-level supervision and enforcement, may lead to divergences in oversight approaches based on resources, priorities, and local legal contexts across Member States."
